Dan,<br><br>
     Although I wasn't in Vietnam  when you were injured,  nor did I get to meet you at Fitzsimmons in Denver.  I spent 8 years working in  military hospitals as a Red Cross Caseworker (included a tour of duty in Vietnam 1971-72 and specialization on the orthopedic wards where amps stayed while getting treatment and waiting for discharge from the service).  I learned alot about courage and honor from men such as yourself.   I have a strong sense of empathy and love for you as an amputee (one of my guys) from Nam.   Here's a virtual hug and Welcome Home!  
